A Government website has beaten The Shard and the 2012 Olympic Cauldron to be named the world’s best design.

Gov.uk saw off nearly 100 competitors in the Design Museum’s Design of the Year 2013.

The basic-looking site features links to pages such as ‘Housing and local services’, ‘Driving and transport’ and ‘Inside Government’.

